    <img src="https://github.com/leesamaya/leesamaya.github.io/raw/main/writing/blog1/DSCF5043.JPG"  alt="Train selfie" 
     style="width:33%; margin-top:20px;">



<p>I wind the car windows down, always. It is a small act, insignificant, though it feels like an act of defiance. The wind tangles my hair, but I don't care. Ah, sweet, sweet Summer! May this euphoria never wear off, the novelty of my new found freedom to drive myself whereever I please. Just think of the all adventures ahead of me!</p>

<p>Today, strawberries: $3 for two. A steal. The gym, a return to my body. The library, long-overdue fashion magazines I only read a couple of pages of. All the little tasks that, together, make a life. In the car, <a href="https://open.spotify.com/track/7nvD9cQj5wYGY44Mhh3My3" target="_blank"><i>Magnetising</i></a> plays: a song like velvet stretched thin over wire. I am someone else now: a French spy with a cigarette in her mouth, driving a stolen car. I am invincible.</p>



